**Door Control and Alarm System**
=====================================

### Hardware Requirements

* 1x PLC (Programmable Logic Controller)
* 1x Lock (Electric or Mechanical)
* 1x Alarm System (Buzzer or Siren)
* 1x Switch (For locking and unlocking)
* 1x Sensor (For detecting door open or closed status)
* 1x Cable connections for all components

### Wiring Diagram
```
  +---------------+
  |  Sensor     |
  +---------------+
           |
           |
           v
  +---------------+
  |  PLC        |
  |  (Programmable  |
  |   Logic  Controller) |
  +---------------+
           |
           |
           v
  +---------------+
  |  Lock       |
  +---------------+
           |
           |
           v
  +---------------+
  |  Alarm      |
  |  (Buzzer or  |
  |   Siren)     |
  +---------------+
           |
           |
           v
  +---------------+
  |  Switch     |
  +---------------+
```
### PLC Program (Structured Text)
```scada
// Define variables for the system
VAR
  // Lock status (0 = locked, 1 = unlocked)
  LOCK_STATUS: BOOL;
  // Alarm status (0 = no alarm, 1 = alarm active)
  ALARM_STATUS: BOOL;
  // Sensor status (0 = door closed, 1 = door open)
  DOOR_STATUS: BOOL;

// Define input and output connections
INPUT
  // Switch input (0 = lock, 1 = unlock)
  LOCK_SWITCH: BOOL;
  // Sensor input (0 = door closed, 1 = door open)
  DOOR_SENSOR: BOOL;
OUTPUT
  // Lock output (0 = lock, 1 = unlock)
  LOCK_OUTPUT: BOOL;
  // Alarm output (0 = no alarm, 1 = alarm active)
  ALARM_OUTPUT: BOOL;

// Main program
PROGRAM
  BEGIN
    // Initialize variables
    LOCK_STATUS := 1;
    ALARM_STATUS := 0;
    DOOR_STATUS := 0;

    // Main loop
    WHILE TRUE DO
      // Check switch input
      IF LOCK_SWITCH THEN
        // Lock the door
        LOCK_OUTPUT := 0;
        LOCK_STATUS := 0;
      ELSE
        // Unlock the door
        LOCK_OUTPUT := 1;
        LOCK_STATUS := 1;
      END_IF;

      // Check sensor input
      IF DOOR_SENSOR THEN
        // Door is open
        DOOR_STATUS := 1;
      ELSE
        // Door is closed
        DOOR_STATUS := 0;
      END_IF;

      // Check if door is open and locked
      IF DOOR_STATUS AND LOCK_STATUS THEN
        // Activate alarm
        ALARM_OUTPUT := 1;
        ALARM_STATUS := 1;
      ELSE
        // Deactivate alarm
        ALARM_OUTPUT := 0;
        ALARM_STATUS := 0;
      END_IF;

      // Delay for 1 second
      DELAY(1000);

    END_WHILE;
  END_PROGRAM;
```
### Explanation

This program is written in Structured Text, a programming language used for PLC programming. The program consists of variables, input and output connections, and a main program loop.

The program initializes the variables and then enters an infinite loop. Inside the loop, it checks the switch input to lock or unlock the door, and the sensor input to detect the door open or closed status. It then checks if the door is open and locked, and if so, activates the alarm.

