**Split and Fill Vertical HTML Divs**

Here's a simple example of how you can split and fill vertical HTML divs using CSS Flexbox.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Split and Fill Vertical Divs</title>
    <style>
        /* Define the container with flexbox layout */
       .container {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            height: 500px;
            border: 1px solid black;
        }

        /* Define the child divs */
       .child {
            flex: 1;
            border: 1px solid black;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="child">Div 1</div>
        <div class="child">Div 2</div>
        <div class="child">Div 3</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

**Explanation:**

*   We define a container div with `display: flex` and `flex-direction: column`, which makes the divs inside it stack vertically.
*   We use the `flex: 1` property to divide the available space evenly among the child divs.

